- Commit after every completed feature or small milestone.
- Commit after creating a new component or API.
- Commit after important bug fixes and Storybook fixes.
- Commit after docs or examples updates.
- Avoid large uncommitted change sets; keep work incremental.
- Keep commits focused and atomic; one concern per commit.
- Never mix unrelated changes in a single commit.
- Ensure project builds (`npm run build`) before committing.
- Ensure Storybook runs (`npm run storybook`) for visual changes.
- Run formatting and linting (`npm run format && npm run lint`) pre-commit.
- Use Conventional Commits: `type(scope): short description`.
- Examples:
  - `feat(button): add loading state`
  - `feat(select): add searchable dropdown`
  - `fix(storybook): resolve Angular decorator issue`
  - `docs(card): improve accessibility examples`
  - `refactor(tokens): simplify semantic naming`
  - `perf(select): optimize virtual scroll rendering`
- Prefer small commits to enable safe rollbacks and bisects.
- Avoid committing unfinished or broken builds.
- Amend or squash only to clean up WIP before merging.
- Use descriptive, professional messages; avoid vague text like "stuff".
- Pair related commits with clear PR titles and descriptions.